fields.description: These beauties set abundant fruit even in cool seasons. Steaming chili awaits you
Melt in your mouth goodness. Beany ganache! Traditionally eaten as a shelly bean.
A celebration unto themselves! Intensely creamy and productive. Dry or Shelly.
Toothsome, creamy and delectable petite white bean. Heavy producer on compact plants.
*Ark Of Taste* Quick cooking, melt in your mouth, comfort food white bean.
Solid producer of rich, creamy beans perfect for soups, spreads, and sauces.
*Ark Of Taste* Early and prolific. Known to make a fierce bowl of chili!
Speckled gold & white beans, pinto size w/rich flavor. Early, large, and prolific.
Creamy white Maine heirloom for authentic baked beans. Wicked good eating!
*Ark Of Taste* Delicious smooth texture & rich flavor. Tasty as shelly beans too!
From Maine. Round, golden brown beans are classic baked or for soup. Very early.
*Ark Of Taste* Small trad. white bean of Tuscany. Dates back to the Etruscans
*Ark Of Taste* 100+yr old Whidbey Is. heirloom. Very reliable, productive & tasty!
*Ark of Taste* Beautiful speckled rose/salmon bean of Tuscany. Early & reliable.
For those who value dry beans for their aesthetic beauty as well as taste.
*Ark Of Taste* Deliciously tender and creamy traditional bean of Tuscany
One of the most renowned beans of Europe. Vigorous 7 vines produce large white beans.
Plump, bicolor burgundy and white pole bean of Russian origin. Early& productive.
Treasured grey/brown and white bean of Seattle food legend Angelo Pellegrini
*Ark of Taste* Famed white bean of Tuscany. Small, tender, and early on 6-7 vines.
Famed plump, glossy black bean of Basque country. Later maturing on vigorous vines
Beautiful Polish variety w/a pink blush at fresh stage. Large beans are prolific and very tender.

Glossy purple, slender, straight, and
 crisp beans. Refreshing full flavor.
Unusually juicy, flat pod wax beans have it all flavor, beauty, and abundance!
6-7"straight pods of stellar tasting green beans Vigorous and productive. White seed.
Very popular tried & true green bean. Known for reliable germination in cooler soils.
Long, flat, golden yellow beans draped on 7 vines. Rich and buttery.
Deeply purple and snappy delicious long pods on strong climbing vines. Italian.
Vigorous leaf growth paired with sweet, beautifully shaped, smooth round golden roots.
Delicious, treasured French variety & the oldest known beet cultivar. Very long tapered roots.
Vigorous trial winner with refined, mild roots and a healthy top of greens.
Tremendous head of greens. Cold hardy with large sweet roots. Excellent keeper.
Uniformly smooth and shapely round red roots w/ lush green, tall tops. Taste test winner!
Bright red roots w/ stunning red and white bulls-eye patterned flesh. Sweet!
Dazzling mix of red, gold, & candy-striped beets. (Shiraz, Touchstone Gold, & Chioggia)
Graceful and branching with early & extensive bud clusters. Milder then "Spring Raab".
Refined variety featuring tight, dark, uniform heads and excellent side shoot production.
Excellent taste, vigor, color, head size & side shoots. Matures over a period of 2 weeks.
Long taproots with a deep, earthy flavor, eaten widely in Japan. Fuzzy plants grow to 3
Superb fall/storage variety producing large green oblong heads. Cold hardy and delicious.
*Ark of Taste* Comically conical sauerkraut favorite, but the flavor is no joke.
Indestructible semi-savoyed green-blushed-red heads in winter. June-July planted.
Uniform, medium sized, round green heads. A split resistant, quick to mature selection.
Excellent N. European variety for fall cropping. Cold hardy med-large green heads.
Blanched leaf stalks of this Artichoke relative are delicious raw, baked, or fried.
Brilliant mix of our orange, purple & yellow carrots. Sure to enthrall everyone. Kids love em!
Beautiful purple tapered roots with, sweet crisp orange centers
A classic carrot. Highly versatile from baby to bunching, fall storage to juicing.
Fun, round, golf ball sized carrots perfect for clay soils & dramatic presentations.
Winter hardy large white domes mature in April. A Spring treat!.
Softball sized roots w/flavor akin to a celery & parsley cross. Excellent storage and taste!
A bright burst of rainbow brilliance in your garden!
Unusual, Oregon-bred glossy leaved variety. Extremely tender, top notch sweet flavor.
Large wavy dark green leaves to scratch that Southern home cookin itch.
Old land- race variety for fabulous, creamy polenta, wonderful breads & corncakes.
Early maturing, compact 5 plants with long slender ears in an amazing spectrum of colors
Wonderful popper with golden kernals
6-7"glossy garnet-black ears on sturdy plants. Kernels pop pure white and delicious
Well bred and soulful with a compelling creaminess. Classic sweetness. White kernels.
Very productive and tasty pickling cuke. Crisp texture and never bitter!
An old Istanbul market favorite, sweet and crisp. Pick 4-5 fruits. Persian type.
Vigorous plants, small round yellow fruits with an irresistible crunch. Kid favorite!
aka Mexican Sour gherkin. Unique fruits look like mini-watermelons w/a lightly pickled flavor
Smooth skinned, long & slender like an English cuke. Crisp & juicy w/no bitterness. Favorite!
Pure white, slicer sized fruits with sweet, never bitter flavor. Compact and very productive.
High quality & productive with everything you love about long green slicing cukes!
Very prolific slender 8-12non-bitter, creamy fruits. Perfect for cool-climate eggplant lovers!
Gorgeous purple & white Italian variety. Plump ruffled teardrop shape. Creamy & productive!

Pick tender young greens for mixes or cook into a nourishing pot of callaloo.
Vigorous strain of this classic salad green. Less deeply lobed leaf & mildly spicy. Cut in 3 wks!
aka "Sylvetta", cold tolerant, slower growing & spicier w/tight rosettes of deeply lobed leaves.

Mild & sweet early-late season Japanese mustard w/graceful fernlike leaves. Prolific!
Finely cut, chartreuse leaves of mild spiciness add loft and a light kick to a salad.
A spicy little number w/delicate deeply lobed leaves and rich purple color.
Very dark green rosettes of mild succulent leaves. Excellent raw or sauted.
Colorful hearty mix of kales, bok choi, tat soi, chards, & ruby streaks. Grow from baby leaf to adult with equal success!
Long stemmed greens with distinctive peppery pungency.
Gorgeous mix of lettuces, mild mustards, arugula, spinach, and specialty greens.
This mix packs a frisky heat with some spicier greens added to our classic mesclun mix.
Slow to bolt upright plants w/succulent, frilled, spicy/sweet leaves. Excellent quality.
Flavorful broadleaf succulent leaves for salads or soup. Milder taste than more finely cut types.
Bright green leaves with deep red veins, and a lemony bite to excite in salads and as garnish.
Delightful greens w/long, slender, antler like leaves, succulent quality and satisfying crunch.
An international soiree of Scotch, Tuscan, and Russian!
Long, narrow dark green savoyed leaves. Excellent flavor & vitamin rich.
Vigorous, cold hardy lacinato type with striking magenta midribs. Bred at Avoca Farm in OR.
Classic cold-hardy curly kale. Sturdy, compact plants w. tasty blue-green leaves.

Oregon-bred variation of Red Russian with hyper frilled leaves. Tender and beautiful.
Long shanked, autumn harvested variety with fantastic flavor. Also popular for baby leeks.

Bolt resistant & crunchy (!) 8"tall upright romaine w/tight dark green, succulent leaves.
Velvety green leaves, large sturdy heads, and buttery texture keep the superlatives rolling!
Red tipped leaves wrap a green, blanched yellow head, soft and delicious.
*Ark Of Taste * 7plants produce miniature 4 heads. Halve & dress. Beautiful.
Green deer-tongue type w. long slender baby leaves, & upright mature heads. Crisp midribs.
Large dark burgundy heads w/deeply textured leaves perfect for holding delicious dressings!
Disease resistant powerhouse with icy-crisp, bright, chartreuse green leaves.
Deep burgundy from the tips of the leaves to the base of the stem. Slow to bolt. Stunning.
Rumpled & folded green leaves painted bright, joyful red to enliven your salads.
Red tinged, densely curled heads. Oakleaf-meets-butterhead tenderness
Striking combination of red speckling on apple green large frames. Excellent taste and texture.
A truly magnificent lettuce of tremendous size! Slow to bolt, crispy and sweet.
Gorgeous red oakleaf variety. Uniform, bolt resistant, and large!
Tight heading mini butter/romaine, with crunchy, sweet, palm sized heads.
Beautiful and huge upright bronze-red romaine. Tender leaves with crunchy midribs.
A volcano of mini savoyed romaine! Dark red tips on green leaves with a pink magma core.
Selection of an old Austrian variety. Very tender apple-green leaves w/red speckles.
Very large, luminescent chartreuse savoyed leaves bred to excel in summer heat.
Adorable palm-sized heads of dense, crunchy romaine. Great for wedge salads!
Colorful mix of all our lettuce varieties including some not yet released
Icebox sized, 4-8lbs, very early and very sweet w/few seeds. Delicious & refreshing!
Early maturing Polish variety with crisp yellow flesh and wonderful sweet flavor!
3-5 lb teardrop shaped w/aromatic,very creamy, sweet flesh.
Yellow football shaped fruits w/sweet flavor reminiscent of honeydew. Very productive.
Drought resistant true cantaloupe w/ethereal, intoxicating fragrance and flesh.
Grapefruit sized w/ delicious honeydew-esque light green flesh. Stores well in fridge.
Classic Japanese winter-hardy bunching onion. Long white stalks and sturdy upright leaves.
Large, productive copper-red Dutch style. Out-stores even the best storage onions!
Dutch-bred yellow onion. Large, round, dense globes store great & taste wonderful.
Unique flat-topped, northern Italian variety. Truly exceptional flavor & excellent keeper.
Enormous (to 3lb!) globe shaped sweet onions. Better storage than most sweets.
Dramatic elongated shape & sweet wine red flesh. Roast! Grill! Eat fresh!
One of the best OP cultivars available. Selected for smooth, straight roots & canker resistance.
*Ark Of Taste* Multicolor Umbrian dry pea eaten in soups and ground for polenta.
Sweet & productive w. 10 peas/pod! Excellent enation and powdery mildew resistance. 2 tall
Medium climber to 3.5. Prolific bearer of fat and superbly sweet pods.
Reigns supreme as the sweetest most flavorful pea! Vigorous 5-6 vines require staking.
Extra-early snap peas on 18-24"vines that dont require staking. Excellent sweet eating!
Unique variety collected in India. 5-6 with purple flowers & sweet golden pods.
Dwarf 2.5 vines yield early and prolifically. Excellent flavor and disease resistance.
6vines of productive, tender, and sweet peas. Lovely bi-color purple/pink blooms.
Treasured med-hot chili of the Basque region known locally as Espelette. Robust flavor!
Pick these smoky little numbers young! Blister in olive oil, sprinkle w/salt, eat. Repeat.
Beautiful and productive long yellow chile originally from Kosovo. Cayenne size & heat

Huge, thick walled peppers w/pointed tips & sweet, rich flavor. Traditional Serbian variety.
*Ark Of Taste* Very sweet, reliable, early maturing, long red Italian frying peppers.
Sweet, bright yellow, popular Polish bell-type w/thick-walled fruits on sturdy upright plants.
Wavy, orange, thin-walled peppers w/ exceptional flavor from Provence. Pickle em!
Bright orange, cylindrical fruits w/fine textured flesh. Highly productive vines, so get baking!

Outstanding savoy leafed strain. Excellent year round & adapted to over-winter conditions.
Excellent and cold hardy smooth-leaf variety. Tender leaves grow exceptionally large.

A summer classic. Prolific, deliciously buttery, bright yellow fruits.
Light green Italian variety w/prominent ribbing & unparalleled flavor. Large vines & flowers.

Very popular, sweet and creamy. 1 lb squashes are perfect to roast and share between two.

Husked tomato relative famous for making salsa verde. Sprawling bushy plants w/purple fruits.

Fabulously sweet & fruity flavor, gorgeous red marbled skin, & elongated fruits!  Indet.
Huge trusses of pink cherries w/rich summertime flavor! Our favorite. Indet.
Tons of very sweet, fruity & delicious orange cherries w/a long harvest period. Yum! Indet.
Ruffled orange 3-5oz beauties w/blushed red blossom end. Early, tasty & productive! Indet.
Wonderfully reliable, productive tomato! 4-5oz orange fruits. Bright juicy flavor. Indet.
We challenge you to find an earlier tomato! 2plants bear 2-4oz fruit w/real flavor. Det.
Fantastically flawless early sets of 4-6oz delicious fruit with balanced flavor. Indet.
Very early, productive & reliable 3-4oz fruits w/ideal balance of sweet/acid. 4 Indet. vines.
Garnet red w/ chesnut shoulders and a lingering fruity richness. Excellent. Indet.

Sweet smelling beneficial insect attracting 3-4 plant with purple blooms.

Perennial herb with deep violet flowers. Make tea and cough syrup w/ aerial parts to treat colds, sore throats, flu

Borage, calendula, bachelors button, and nasturtiums to gussy up your meals & desserts!

Stunning simplicity in pure white!

3' stately, bushy plants with long straight stems adorned with showy white bracts.

Stunning & unpredictable array of colors, shapes, and sizes. Expect to be delighted!!
All youve been dreaming of! Fluffy, teddy bear type to 7 w/many long-lasting blooms.

All the subtlety of a drag queen in a sequined mini dress and just as *fabulous*.
Dusty rose blooms with vibrant lime-green centers on long cutting stems.
One of the more elegant and subdued of the Zinnia palate! A lovely bouquet addition.

Versatile, graceful, & wavy purple-green lance-leaved plants.  19th cent. French cultivar.

Lovely & plump golden-hued wax beans.
Wildly vigorous, very long, straight roots. Mild & sweet flavor.
